option::Option::<T>::as_mut.doc:
Converts from `&mut Option<T>` to `Option<&mut T>`.

# Examples

```
let mut x = Some(2);
match x.as_mut() {
    Some(v) => *v = 42,
    None => {},
}
assert_eq!(x, Some(42));
```

src:
pub const fn insert(&mut self, value: T) -> &mut T
    where
        T: [const] Destruct,
    {
        *self = Some(value);

        // SAFETY: the code above just filled the option
        unsafe { self.as_mut().unwrap_unchecked() }
    }

